org.naomi.regex

Class CollectionCharClass

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.naomi.regex.Pattern
      • org.naomi.regex.CharClass
        • org.naomi.regex.CollectionCharClass
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AlterationListener

    public class CollectionCharClass
extends CharClass
    An instance of CollectionCharClass is a Pattern which, on each repetition, matches any single character in the Collection of Characters used to instantiate the CollectionCharClass. Any duplicates in the Collection are ignored. If the collection contains more than a few thousand characters, performance may be adversely impacted. The internal "Not" flag in each instance can be set to make the class instead match all characters except those in the pre-defined set denoted by its instantiating Collection; this has the effect of matching the complement of the specified set of characters.

    Example: 

      // Define a java.util.HashMap and add some characters to it
  //   (the keys of the map are the literal character values)


     Map<Character,String> char2Name = new HashMap<>();
     char2Name.put(' ' , "SPACE");
     char2Name.put('$' , "DOLLAR");
     char2Name.put('(', "LEFT");

  // Create a CharClass of the characters in the java.util.Set char2Name.keySet()

     CharClass namedChars = new CollectionCharClass(char2Name.keySet());
